<p>I agree - many museums do not connect dots, and do not inspire new conclusions.</p>

<p>There are some museums that promote viewer analysis and spark new conclusions.  For example, the Holocaust museum in Washington D.C. evaluates, through strong copy and powerful artifacts, the social, political, and economic factors that gave rise to the holocaust.  Every exhibit is well integrated with other exhibits on the timeline.</p>

